1 3. Successful passage of a CALT competency examination or CERI
2 competency examination; and
3 4. Twenty-eight (28) days of instruction post the passage of
4 the applicable competency examination.
5 C. A certified teacher who earns a CALT micro-credential or a
6 CERI micro-credential shall be authorized to assess students for and
7 diagnose dyslexia.
8 D. A micro-credential awarded pursuant to this section shall be
9 reflected on a teacher’s certificate to teach.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
11 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
15 Passed the Senate the 27th day of March, 2025.
